    <div class="issue-card">
      <div class="issue-title">⚠️ Instagram Requires Business Account</div>
      <div class="issue-desc">Instagram Graph API only allows posting to Business/Creator accounts linked to a Facebook Page. Personal accounts return a 403 error.</div>
      <div class="issue-fix"><strong>Fix:</strong> Convert Instagram to Business account (free, in app) → Link to Facebook Page → then API works.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="issue-card">
      <div class="issue-title">⚠️ Facebook Token Expires in 60 Days</div>
      <div class="issue-desc">Long-lived tokens last ~60 days. After expiry, posting fails with error 190. No auto-refresh in this workflow.</div>
      <div class="issue-fix"><strong>Fix:</strong> Set a calendar reminder to exchange token every 50 days using the token exchange curl command above. Production: add a scheduled n8n sub-workflow to auto-refresh.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="issue-card">
      <div class="issue-title">⚠️ Leonardo AI Generation Takes 15–45s</div>
      <div class="issue-desc">Fixed 15-second wait may be insufficient for complex prompts. If image fetch returns "PENDING", the workflow gets an empty URL.</div>
      <div class="issue-fix"><strong>Fix:</strong> Increase Wait node to 30s for safety. Better: implement polling loop (n8n Loop node → check status every 5s until COMPLETE).</div>
    </div>

    <div class="issue-card">
      <div class="issue-title">⚠️ Gemini May Wrap JSON in Markdown</div>
      <div class="issue-desc">Gemini sometimes returns ```json ... ``` fences around the JSON, breaking JSON.parse().</div>
      <div class="issue-fix"><strong>Fix:</strong> Already handled — Parse node strips fences with regex before parsing. Prompt also says "no markdown". Stable in 95%+ of runs.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="issue-card" style="border-left-color: var(--muted);">
      <div class="issue-title" style="color:var(--muted)">ℹ️ LinkedIn & YouTube — Content Generated, Not Auto-Posted</div>
      <div class="issue-desc">LinkedIn Marketing API requires Partner Program approval. YouTube API requires an actual video file to upload — this workflow generates a video prompt only.</div>
      <div class="issue-fix"><strong>Workaround:</strong> All 4 platform captions are generated and logged to Google Sheets. LinkedIn/YouTube content can be copy-pasted manually. Auto-posting these two requires API partner access.</div>
    </div>

